# Trade Filter Feature — Rules & Architecture

## What This Feature Does

Allows a contractor or subcontractor to scope a takeoff to their specific trade(s) before the plan is processed. Instead of returning every material in a full set, Claude extracts only the categories relevant to the selected trade.

This is implemented as a **prompt-side filter (Option B)** — Claude is told upfront what to extract, not post-filtered after the fact. This produces better accuracy for the selected trade because context is focused.

---

## File Map

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `server/claude/trade-definitions.js` | TRADE_MAP, TRADE_ORDER, getTradeFilter() |
| `server/claude/build-prompts.js` | buildTradeFilterBlock(), updated buildCustomProjectSystemPrompt() |
| `server/routes/projects.js` | Reads tradeFilter from request body, passes to runTakeoff() |
| `client/src/components/projects/LaunchTakeoffWidget.tsx` | Single/multi trade selector UI |

